		<credit project="CfPBoK@https://slebok.github.io/cfpbok/"/>
		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2010"></a><br><code>sle2010/paper02</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2010</a> paper:</span><br><i>Reference Attribute Grammars for Metamodel Semantics</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/ChristoffBürger.html">Christoff Bürger</a>, <a href="../profile/SvenKarol.html">Sven Karol</a>, <a href="../profile/ChristianWende.html">Christian Wende</a>, <a href="../profile/UweAßmann.html">Uwe Aßmann</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_3">10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_3</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1c.html"><span class="tagM">T1C: Behavioural Semantics</span></a><ul><li> The paper focuses on specifying (and evaluating) model semantics for EMF metamodels using reference attribute grammars.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagL">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> It leverages RAGs as the formalism/metalanguage for semantics specification.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It introduces JastEMF as tool support integrating EMF with the JastAdd RAG system.
</li></ul></li></ul>
